channel.title: Need help with a program called GZIP (a program for adding models 2 ur client)
channel.description:
Ok i followed kevins tutorial on rune-server and im gettin stuck on a part. I installed gzip. Then i went to run>cmd then typed [code]cd c:\Program Files\GnuWin32\bin[/code]
It then gave me this...
[code]Microsoft Windows XP [Version 5.1.2600] (C) Copyright 1985-2001 Microsoft Corp.
C:\Documents and Settings\Justin>cd c:\Program Files\GnuWin32\bin
C:\Program Files\GnuWin32\bin>
[/code]
I then typed in
[code]gzip filetozip.mdl[/code]
I then got this error....
[code]Microsoft Windows XP [Version 5.1.2600] (C) Copyright 1985-2001 Microsoft Corp.
C:\Documents and Settings\Justin>cd c:\Program Files\GnuWin32\bin
C:\Program Files\GnuWin32\bin>gzip filetozip.mdl gzip: filetozip.mdl: No such file or directory
C:\Program Files\GnuWin32\bin> [/code]
Thats wut aprt im stuck on plz hlep me....
If you don't understand what i'm talknig about go here http://www.rune- server.org/showthread.php?t=28358
[size=17pt]Or does any1 recmend a different program besides gzip?[/size]

item.title: Need help with a program called GZIP (a program for adding models 2 ur client)
item.dc:creator: @system system
item.description:
@system wrote:

heres something i made just put this in C:\Program Files\GnuWin32\bin

and whenever you need it just type the filename and fileextention and it will gzip it to C:\Program Files\GnuWin32\bin
and it should be [filename].[fileextention].gz

@echo off
:a
echo welcome to blitz_9100 gzipper
echo put in the file name below
cd C:\Program Files\GnuWin32\bin\
set /p n=file:
gzip %n%
echo gzipped %n% at %time% and on %date% . >> gzipped.txt
echo successfully gzipped %n%
echo check C:\Program Files\GnuWin32\bin for the file
pause>nul
goto a

hope this helps
